Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Chop your @new potatoes{2} in half widthways and then in half once again. Toss the potatoes in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a good pinch of @salt and @pepper. Place them on a #baking tray{} on the top shelf of the oven for around ~{25%minutes}.

> They're ready when they are browned off and soft in the middle - test them!

Put your feet up for ~{10%minutes}.

Boil a medium sized #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Pour in your @fresh peas{} and cook for around ~{4%mins}, or until they're soft enough to eat. Drain the peas and mash them up with a #fork{}, add @Greek style yoghurt{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt and @pepper.

> If you have a blender then stick them in there with 2 tbsp of the boiling water.

Heat a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season the @sea bream fillets{4} on both sides with a pinch of @salt and @pepper. Once the oil is really hot lay the fish carefully in the pan, skin-side down.

Leave the fish to cook for around ~{3%mins} on the skin side without touching it. After 3 mins carefully turn the fish over and cook for another ~{2%mins}. Add @?butter{1%tsp} into the pan at the end and squeeze in the juice of @lemon{1/2}.

Spoon the pan juices over the fish and then serve with your potatoes, mushy peas and a drizzle of @malt vinegar{1} - lovely!